title: Business Improvement Districts, Washington DC, 2002
name: Business Improvement Districts, Washington DC, 2002
description:
Business Improvement Districts (BID). The dataset contains locations and attributes of the six BID jurisdictions (Downtown, Golden Triangle, Mt. Vernon Triangle, Adams Morgan, Georgetown, and NoMa), first authorized under the Business Improvement Districts Act of 1996, created as part of the DC Geographic Information System (DC GIS) for the D.C. Office of the Chief Technology Officer (OCTO) and participating D.C. government agencies. This layer also contains the Mt. Vernon Community Improvement District (CID).

Jurisdictions were identified from public records (websites, legacy GIS data, real property records) and heads-up digitized from the snapbase.

author.source: D.C. Office of the Chief Technology Officer (OCTO)
